The patch introduces a new native Python error import without updating the native stub, causing Python type checking to fail. This is actionable and affects the repository's required verification path.

Review comment:

- [P2] Add the missing ProjectionDestructiveError stub — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15d/src/python/fathomdb/errors.py:101-103
  When Python type checking is run, this new import fails because `ProjectionDestructiveError` is added to the native module at runtime but not declared in `src/python/fathomdb/_fathomdb.pyi`. In environments that run `agent-typecheck.sh`/pyright, this surfaces as `"ProjectionDestructiveError" is unknown import symbol`, so the new typed error needs a matching class entry in the stub alongside the other native errors.
